{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a87d6713-727c-4ab6-90a4-8275026aba36","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-code-coverage \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `-- --report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `-- --collect-code-coverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `-- --crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `-- --hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `-- --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nPlatform-specific args go after `--`. The `--filter` stays before it (the VSTest bridge forwards it).\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\nFor **Cobertura output** specifically, configure it in a `.runsettings` file or pass `--collect-code-coverage-output-format cobertura` after the `--`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19a92eea-07c3-42c0-b8bc-174967b5898a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task. Let me provide the answer directly.\n\nKey changes when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the arguments change\n2. `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same, but using `--treenode-filter` is the new native way, though `--filter` is still supported via compatibility layer)\n3. `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` \n\n\n4. Code coverage collection changes from `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` to `--collect code-coverage` when using Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you'll need a different approach\n5. Blame diagnostics shift from `--blame-crash`, `--blame-hang`, and `--blame-hang-timeout` to `--crashdump`, `--hangdump`, and `--hangdump-timeout` respectively\n\nYou can run the test executable directly or continue using `dotnet test`, but the argument syntax differs between the two approaches.\n\nWhen sticking with `dotnet test` on Microsoft.Testing.Platform projects, `--filter` remains compatible through the VSTest bridge or you can use `--treenode-filter` instead, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` (needs Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport), code coverage uses `--collect code-coverage` (requires Microsoft.CodeCoverage), and the blame options map to `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with their respective timeout variants. When passing these arguments through `dotnet test`, you separate them with `--` before the actual flags. I need to reconsider the filter syntax and NuGet package requirements for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8. The platform uses `--treenode-filter` natively, though `--filter` works through a compatibility layer. I also need to list out the specific NuGet packages required: the core platform, TRX reporting extension, code coverage extension, and crash dump extension.\n\nFor the actual command, I'm settling on using `dotnet test` with the `--filter` flag for category-based filtering, then passing platform-specific arguments after `--` including TRX reporting, code coverage collection, and crash dump generation.","outputTokens":1565,"requestId":"7C16:171772:2621AF1:2A3AFE1:69F9409A"},"id":"2b02b9db-4a4d-4e06-beea-68d047c7aa83","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:58:29.032Z","parentId":"3ec23b62-0324-42f2-8b41-634176f6c304"}
